17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Section 1, Chapter 281, O.S.L.
19 2023, as amended by Section 1, Chapter 354, O.S.L. 2024 (70 O.S.
20 Supp. 2025, Section 5-148.1), is amended to read as follows:
21 Section 5-148.1. A. The State Department of Education shall
22 establish and maintain a three-year five-year pilot program known as
23 the School Resource Officer Program.
24
Req. No. 16422 Page 1

1 B. School resource officers employed or contracted by school
2 districts participating in the School Resource Officer Program shall
3 successfully complete law enforcement active shooter emergency
4 response training given by the Council on Law Enforcement Education
5 and Training (CLEET) and approved by the Department of Public
6 Safety.
7 C. 1. A school district participating in the School Resource
8 Officer Program shall give first priority to employing or
9 contracting with a law enforcement officer with sworn authority and
10 training in school-based law enforcement and crisis response who is
11 assigned by an employing law enforcement agency to work
12 collaboratively with one or more schools using community-oriented
13 policing concepts.
14 2. If a law enforcement agency that serves the area in which a
15 school district is located is unwilling or unable to provide a law
16 enforcement officer described in paragraph 1 of this subsection, a
17 participating school district may employ or contract with a retired
18 law enforcement officer or an armed security guard who is licensed
19 pursuant to the Oklahoma Security Guard and Private Investigator
20 Act. The law enforcement agency that serves the area in which the
21 school district is located shall preauthorize any individual
22 employed or contracted with under this paragraph. The school shall
23 require a background check on the individual. The law enforcement
24 agency that serves the area in which the school district is located
Req. No. 16422 Page 2

1 shal l allow an authorized individual employed or contracted with the
2 school district access to the preauthorizing agency's radio system,
3 pursuant to this paragraph, and a police band radio system which may
4 be used by the individual in the performance of his or her duties to
5 be paid for by the employing district. A school district may use
6 funds from the School Security Revolving Fund created pursuant to
7 Section 5-148.2 of this title to cover the cost of the radio system.
8 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY Section 2, Chapter 281, O.S.L.
9 2023, as amended by Section 2, Chapter 408, O.S.L. 2024 (70 O.S.
10 Supp. 2025, Section 5-148.2), is amended to read as follows:
11 Section 5-148.2. A. There is hereby created in the State
12 Treasury a revolving fund for the State Department of Education to
13 be designated the "School Security Revolving Fund". The fund shall
14 be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and
15 shall consist of all monies received by the State Department of
16 Education from:
17 1. Reimbursements, grants, or other monies received from other
18 state agencies and entities for school security;
19 2. Reimbursements, grants, or other monies received from the
20 United States government obligated to school security projects;
21 3. Gifts, donations, and bequests; and
22 4. Monies appropriated or apportioned by the Legislature.
23
24
Req. No. 16422 Page 3

1 B. All monies accruing to the credit of the School Security
2 Revolving Fund are hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and
3 expended by the State Department of Education for the purposes of:
4 1. Establishing and maintaining a School Resource Officer
5 Program; and
6 2. Providing physical security enhancements for schools
7 including, but not limited to, school resource officers, cameras,
8 gates, lighting, locks, doors, windows, security geofencing,
9 ballistic storm shelters, and mobile panic alert systems.
10 Monies in the School Security Revolving Fund shall supplement
11 and not supplant existing school security funding.
12 C. Expenditures from the School Security Revolving Fund shall
13 be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer against claims
14 filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of
15 Management and Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
16 Expenditures from the School Security Revolving Fund shall not
17 exceed Fifty Million Dollars ($50,000,000.00) Seventy-five Million
18 Dollars ($75,000,000.00) in any fiscal year and. Expenditures shall
19 be divided equally among every public school district in the state
20 and shall be distributed to school districts based on the number of
21 school sites in the district.
22 D. The provisions of this section shall not apply to virtual
23 schools.
24 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
Req. No. 16422 Page 4

1 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
2 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
3 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
4 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
